(Description:)221 2620 MS
(The standard library uses default arguments to member functions of template classes that are dependent on)521 2665 MS
(template arguments in a number of places, even though such defaults are not currently legal C++.  This)521 2710 MS
(clash between the language and the library is currently resolved \(17.3.4.4 paragraph 4\) by specifying that)521 2755 MS
(default arguments are to be treated as equivalent overloadings with additional functions. This is called the)521 2800 MS
("Plum Patch".)521 2845 MS
