(Defaults can be removed from the library by either eliminating the default case, or providing an additional)521 261 MS
(overload.)521 306 MS
(There are at least 41 signatures affected.  Because some of these include multiple defaults, there are a total)521 396 MS
(of 54 cases.)521 441 MS
(An additional signature would have to be added to the library to deal with each of the cases, a total of 54)521 531 MS
(new signatures in all.)521 576 MS
(Of the 41 signatures affected, 29 are constructors.  Because the classes involved already have several)521 666 MS
(constructors, adding additional constructors is particularly confusing.  The use of default arguments makes)521 711 MS
(these classes easier to understand and easier to use.)521 756 MS
(Proposed Resolution:)221 846 MS
(Default arguments for member functions of template classes should either be added to the language or)521 891 MS
(removed from the library.  The "Plum Patch" is not intended to be a permanent solution to the problem.)521 936 MS
(The core working group continues to investigate a language change while the library working group)521 981 MS
(continues to investigate library changes.)521 1026 MS
