(to widen the candidate digit values \(once\) to )521 1086 MS
(char_type, and then compare the input character values)1208 1086 MS
(directly.  This allows the time-consuming operations to be done once, on the first conversion, and then used)521 1131 MS
(on subsequent conversions. This does have different semantics: only the canonical digit or sign character in)521 1176 MS
(the )521 1221 MS
(codeset is recognised.)578 1221 MS
