(Is this meant to be legal C++?  The answer depends on whether the expansion of the list template tries to)521 1216 MS
(allocate a field of type S in the class list<S>.  If so, it would violate paragraph 9.2.8 which states that non-)521 1261 MS
(static members of a class must be objects of previously defined classes.  However, I couldn't find anything)521 1306 MS
(in the draft standard that states that list<S> may or may not expand into a class with a field of type S.)521 1351 MS
